item.description:
You are invited to a local NHLA get together!


When: Wednesday, August 29 at 7:00 p.m.

Where: Plaistow Public Library, 85 Main Street, Plaistow, NH
Map


Eileen Landies, chairperson of the NHLA, will review the NHLA's mission and background, and discuss the NHLA's upcoming goals for promoting liberty in New Hampshire. Eileen promises to talk about all the ways that you can help the cause of liberty through the NHLA.

Bring a friend, or encourage a friend in your area to come!


Light refreshments will be served.
Doors open at 6:45pm.
item.name: NHLA's Chairperson Eileen Landies to give talk in Plaistow
